article.description: Celeste Hoewisch scored 14 of her 20 points in the first half and Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) took a big lead early in cruising to an 84-25 victory over Youngstown State on Saturday.
article.headline: Wisconsin-Green Bay opens 26-0 lead in rout of Youngstown St.
article.linkText: Phoenix open 26-0 lead; rout of Youngstown St.
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. --  Celeste Hoewisch scored 14 of her 20 points in the first half and Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) took a big lead early in cruising to an 84-25 victory over Youngstown State on Saturday.

Julie Wojta had 13 of her 17 in the first half as the Phoenix (22-1, 11-0 Horizon League) built a 26-0 lead and had a 49-8 halftime cushion in winning their 13th straight game. The eight points were the fewest in a half in Youngstown State history.

The Penguins started the game 0 for 13 with seven turnovers before Brandi Brown got them on the board on a 3-pointer with 8:07 left in the first half.

Brown, the Horizon League's leading scorer, had 15 points for Youngstown State (3-19, 1-10).

Lydia Bauer scored 12 points off the bench and Hannah Quilling added 10 for Wisconsin-Green Bay.
